<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 0px 269px 300px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss b174ef864cda601f37d52e9ca06b1dc7-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Year 2 and 3 Aftercare Expectations</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>At the end of the extended period of aftercare in Years 2 and 3, the operator, operations team or the facility manager should:</p>
<ol>
<li>Continue its performance evaluation</li>
<li>
<strong>Prepare the annual reports on performance</strong> with an explanation of improvements, changes and good or bad performance</li>
<li>Prepare reports on the <strong>performance of materials and equipment</strong>
</li>
<li>At the end of each year, <strong>feedback the findings of performance evaluation</strong> to the design and construction team and the Appointing Party's Information Manager</li>
<li>Retain data on measured performance to inform the benchmarking of required outcomes and performance targets for future projects</li>
<li>Request the attendance of a senior representative of each of the main disciplines within the design and construction team at a workshop with the Appointing Party's Information Manager and the representative(s) of end-users</li>
<li>
<strong>Report to the Appointing Party on performance during the year</strong>, the actions considered necessary to optimize the performance of the asset/facility <strong>and the lessons learned</strong>
</li>
</ol></div></div></div></div></div></div>